This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by former President Barack Obama in June 2014. The memorandum emphasizes the importance of workplace flexibilities and work-life programs in attracting and retaining a talented workforce. It directs federal agencies to promote a culture where employees are aware of these programs and how they can improve productivity and engagement. The memorandum also outlines specific actions that agencies should take, such as reviewing and amending procedures for requesting work schedule flexibilities, expanding access to workplace flexibilities, and encouraging the use of work-life programs. The Director of the Office of Personnel Management (OPM) is tasked with providing guidance and support to agencies in implementing these measures. The memorandum also includes provisions for agency reviews of workplace flexibilities and work-life policies, as well as general provisions regarding the authority of agencies and the Director of the Office of Management and Budget.